   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>Ptolemaios to his dearest Harbekis, greeting. I want you to know that (he/she) said that De . . ., also called Belles, will await tomorrow in the ship of my brother, Typhis. When you have left, he has had a better hope of wheat. I have written to Ankis and . . .</ab>
         </div>
